event,"The dreams they never stop, sometimes the bottle is the only way to keep them quite. Sometimes we do so well in our lives we fight the pain we hide inside, and for no reason there she stands in our min in our dreasm just as real as day and you wake up a little sadder then the day before not just because she is not there but because no one is there and it dawns on you that your alone, always alone. Trust is such a simple thing you would think, people used to put it above everything else and now what. It is said but never really meant, for sometimes it becomes to hard to be real any longer. ""I am different. I am here for you when you need me always."" The words ring out over and over, I have heard it so many times before but its never real."
event,"Just so everyone up in VA knows I don
column2: t know if I will be back up there anytime in the next year or two or three. I am buying a house in Nov down here in FL and my parents are more then likely coming down here for X-Mas since it is much warmer and all. I am in starting my Business program in Sept and while I have weekends off and I have no classes past 9pm I am still going to be at school everyday and no vacations. I have time off next 4th of July and I might ""MIGHT"" be up there then. But then once I graduate next July I am taking 2 weeks off and going to Italy with my family we are going to find the village where my family comes from. Then I am back right into the swing of things with my cafe and working on my MBA so the next 3 or 4 years are really kinda crazy so we shall see. I'm not really planning on coming back up there, I mean there is nothing for me to do when I am up there and being up there makes me depressed. But everyone knows you have an open invite down here I mean I am 40min from Daytona and 35 from Coco Beach an hour from Tampa and 15min from Disney. And most definitly when I get the house in the fall it is really open for guests. SO yea thats another quick update about whats going on."

column1: event,"So here I am, Full Sail is just about done. I can't believe its been a year. I can't believe there are things that I miss about CNU,the red lights and talks at night with a few people to be specific. One in particular who I really do miss her words of critical thoughts on my action helped me through a bit or rough times. But here I am a bit older and wiser, into button ups and dress pants now getting into the business of life. Speaking of business I am planning on going for my MBA after I get done with the Entertainment Business program, and let me tell you studying for GMAT's are not a fun thing. Anyways thats all for now talk to people soon."

event,"Well it has been a hell of a long time since I have done an update on here so lets see where to start. I'm still in Florida, and I am going to be staying here for a while it looks like. I am buying a house in October after the hurricane season. Elise and I are not together anymore, about a month and a half ago she pulled her same old shit and on my birthday to make things even worse. I just wish I had done the clean break when I first came down here like I had planned instead of putting in another year of energy and money.

School is I don't want to say hard but its very time consuming and there is a lot of technical stuff to digest. And you can get by with the little effort but I want to know exactly how all the stuff works so. Actually I can't say its to easy my class started with about 112 kids we are down to 48 in 10 months so we have lost a few. But the materials interesting even the math we do is all related to acoustics and delays and stuff so its cool. Right now I am in Advanced Workstations (Advanced Pro Tools training) and Busines Law. I love Business Law, absolutly love it, and the class couldn't have come at a better time. Here is where the next big news comes into play, I am going to be opening my own cafe with live venue down here with in the next year. I have been working on the business plan I already have 2 private investors interested so yea in a years time I will hopefuly be in full swing with running my own cafe. Don't worry I will let everyone know when it opens and you can all come to the opening lol.

Aside from that I have been interning at a studio called Phat Planet, nothing to grand aside from that. Just getting by one day at a time with very little sleep. Also the social life thing is lacking but thats because I am so busy. Something odd I actually found myself missing CNU, not the classes and all but the environment, I kinda miss the college feel this place is not like a college at all, that and its so hard to be unique here everyone is so creative, the way they dress the things they do there bodies it kinda makes you just give up and dress down.
If anyone wants to visit the offer is still open, actually I haven
column2: t had anyone come down and say hi yet but you are all busy to, but hopefuly once I have the house some more ppl will come down. I am only an hour from Daytona, and hour from Tampa and like 15 min from Disney and there is almost always stuff to do down here. Wow I should really get out more lol

column1: Anyways thats all for now there is a ton of other stuff thats probably going on but that would take a while to fill ppl in so later"

column1: event,"Where to start this one there is actually so much I want to say and not sure how to start it all off.

I'm still not over her and I think I know why now. Loving her is the first real true thing I ever let myself do. I mean truely it is the only real emotion I can think back and see me giving myself into totaly. Thats the poblem. In my dreams she still lives a pice of her, her face etched into my head. But at the same time such a pure form of hatrid for her and distane for her as well. Love and hate such powerful things it has casued me to become bitter to women in general,  and think of them as nothing but whores which for the most part appears to be true. Or at least to the effect the7y are not trustworthy.

But on the drive home I was thinking I hate people, well I hate god to. So thats a lot to hate and I am alone. But I hate myself as well most of all almost, which yes yes is sad or stupid of me or what ever it is you are thinking. Its a shame I think back and remember to when I was young and honor, passion, truth , justice, higher causes they were the heart of who I was. To be great meant to do what was nobel to me where has that all gone. ""Starring down the barrel of a 45""

I remember back in high school one day in supply I was talking to Pam and Eric and I was saying fuck this being good, I am tired of being the good guy all the time. And its funny how we become things we imagine and things we hate. And almost no matter what we become we dislike, and find I don
column3: t know about ourselves. ""And be a simple kind of man""

Kenny and Matt lol strange enough I miss you guys in your own right. Kenny to me you and I made no sense we come from two different worlds I mean totaly different, and we always had that final fight that I think  was just stressing and hiding out form coming between us. Matt what to say about you, so much potential there, honestly. The only thing for you is becoming aware more of what else is out there so eager like a child in more ways in one that become a good quality.

Funny thing about you four and myself and the rest of us this journey we call life how it all fits how we all move like pieces to game in and out further and further apart we drift only to come crashing together or stuffed in a bag at the end. Remember what it is like to be a walnut.
The more the world consumes me I just close my eyes, its seems I run away but finally for the last time.

event,"Yes well what to say. Got back from a week in Florida on Sunday. Full Sail is amazing I mean it is more then I thought it would be I can't wait till classes start in Sept. Found a great apartment in a really nice area, just need to find a room mate now and figure out how to pay for it all. The rental of a moving truck is like $700 + gas = broke. But it will be well worth it I know it will i just need to get out of here and down to there, really wish is was end of summer already.

The 21st birthday was dull but that is normal for my birthdays, around noon I tracked down some friends and we went and played pool for a few hours. Great thing being able to order a beer and drink it legaly at a bar gonna take some getting used to :).  Then oh so classic we dressed up in dockers shorts and polo shirts tucked in and all we looked like we belonged in a country club, picked up a bottle of white wine and played croquet for the next 2 hours. It was really a site to see, especally given Kevin and myself and our normal attire. That was about it for the birthday, nothing exciting got a call from 2 people and got 2 birthday cards and umm yea so much for turning 21 being great.

Now what is going on is just a lot of packing and cleaning and deciding whats being thrown away and whats coming with me on this move to Florida, its amazing how much junk I have picked up in the past 21 years. For some reason I found reports from middle school that for some reason I saved. Little sad at some points of the packing came across some things of my Angels, I do still miss her that will never change but I am moving on trying to at least. Just need someone who can be patient with me. Yea really a lot of junk though then of course I am fixing some old furniture of my parents re painting it and what not so I don
column2: t move into an empty apartment.Start working at Busch Gardens on the 24th looking foward to that I really need the money. Thats about it for now. Hope everyone is having a good summer, make sure you go out and get some sun."

column1: event,"Not so simple is it moving on. The world is so small sometimes, it never feels like we can escape our life if even for a moment. But the moment we do we will be so far gone we will miss all that we had. Time stops, hearts skip a beat, I breathe and everything clears up. I always claimed to be so strong so independent, that when anything came there I would be standing taller then ever while everyone else lost self, and now I fear.

My Sweetness came by tonight. I will miss her. She has found a place in my heart somehow when I wasn't even really looking, from this day foward no matter what I am doing or where I am I will drop it all for her. And she says she will never ask me to and the whole point is she shall never have to. Honestly this is a special place you hold now with in me I could never even hope to find the words to explain it. This was never planned I mean, no expectations of you taking this place ever lived in me not like this.

Back to the move, I wish it was Aug already or Oct so I could start this year over from scratch maybe do things differently. The start of this semester would have been different for sure. Life moves on we fold in and out right?
I am folding and unfolding. I am ready."""
